review_text: A normal metro station on the blue line. Next to the bus stops and on busy street.....
Not too clean but ok
Everything is nearby this metro station like McDonald's, Tim hortons, grocery stores and so on.
I really like this metro station. It is right next to the train and the bus stops. Many exits. On busy streets like Jean Talon or Ave du Parc. Very practical.
Sale degeulasse
Nice
Great
This is a very normal metro station.

(Translated by Google) Nice station because the station is built really well but Ilya defeat poor people so it is a bit dirty.

(Translated by Google) Despite a shabby appearance, this station is quite useful for the city. Traveling north-south is much faster from this station than any other and as a bonus you end up downtown near McGill. The Indian-style district is to be discovered and the Gare Parc is nearby.

(Original)
Malgré un aspect miteux, cette station est bien utile pour la ville. Effectuer un trajet Nord-Sud est bien plus rapide de cette station que n'importe quelle autre et en boni vous vous retrouvez au centre-ville près de McGill. Le quartier de style indien est à découvrir et la Gare Parc est tout près.

(Translated by Google) Station not very clean at street level. Several beggars on site. Too bad for this station with the beautiful architecture of the old Jean-Talon station.

(Original)
Station pas très propre au niveau de la rue. Plusieurs quêteux sur place. Dommage pour cette station à la belle architecture de l'ancienne gare Jean-Talon.

(Translated by Google) Beautiful metro with a history ... Pay attention to the works of art in the architecture and the rays of sun reflected on the polished ground please.
There is a fruit shop open until 4am in front of the metro! A hidden gem of the metropolis ...

Zos and Renaud

Montreal, August 24, 2016

(Original)
